Resistance bands offer a versatile and convenient way to add resistance to strength training exercises. Secure one end of the resistance band under your foot and hold the other end with your hand. Perform various exercises such as rows, chest presses, or shoulder raises. Control the resistance band throughout the movement. Aim for 10-12 reps for each exercise.

• Secure one end of the resistance band under your foot and hold the other end with your hand.
• Perform various exercises such as rows, chest presses, or shoulder raises.
• Control the resistance band throughout the movement.
• Aim for 10-12 reps for each exercise.
